.TH ABRAFLEXI-MATCHER 1 "July 17, 2026" "abraflexi-matcher" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
abraflexi-matcher \- Match all capable received and issued invoices in AbraFlexi
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B abraflexi-matcher
[OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B abraflexi-matcher
runs the full legacy matching pass: it matches unpaid received invoices
against outgoing payments, then matches unpaid issued invoices against
incoming payments (variable symbol and specific symbol combined), in one
run. It is equivalent to running
.BR abraflexi-matcher-in (1)
followed by
.BR abraflexi-matcher-out (1).
.PP
For new deployments, prefer the split matchers
.BR abraflexi-match-varsym (1),
.BR abraflexi-match-specsym (1)
and
.BR abraflexi-match-accountno (1),
which report their matching method separately and can be scheduled
independently.
.SH OPTIONS
This script uses environment variables for configuration.
.TP
.B RESULT_FILE
Path to the output JSON report file.
.TP
.B MATCHER_DAYS_BACK
Number of days to look back for payments (default: 365)
.TP
.B MATCHER_LOCALIZE
Locale for log/report messages: en_US (default), cs_CZ, or sk_SK.
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_OVERPAY
Document type code used to automatically settle overpayments; empty (default) = do not settle overpayments automatically.
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_PARTIAL_MATCH
Settle underpaid invoices (partial payments) automatically instead of leaving them for manual review (default: false)
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The script requires AbraFlexi connection details:
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_URL
AbraFlexi server URL
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_LOGIN
AbraFlexi login username
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_PASSWORD
AbraFlexi password
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_COMPANY
AbraFlexi company code
.SH FILES
.TP
.I match_report.json
Default output file containing the matching results in JSON format compliant with the multiflexi report schema.
